# AdvCpp Standards

## Memory and lifetime

- No `malloc`/`free`; avoid raw `new`/`delete` — use RAII and smart pointers.
- Classes owning dynamic memory follow rule of 3/5.

## API design

- `const` methods where state is not mutated (e07).
- Pass inputs as `const&`; avoid unnecessary copies (e06).
- Lean public APIs — no methods not required by interface/assignment (e08).
- Error handlers take structured `ErrorRef`/codes — not ad-hoc diagnostic strings (e05).

## Structure

- Short functions, single responsibility (e09).
- Unrelated classes not grouped in one header (e01).
- Minimal `#includes`; forward-declare when possible (e17).
- Free helpers in anonymous namespace in `.cpp`, not public class API.
- No duplicate logic across components (e10).

## Values

- No magic numbers — named constants (e23).
- No repeated expensive computation — cache or compute once (e21).

## Includes DAG

Headers should not create cycles. Implementation details stay in `.cpp`.
